<item>
            <title>[MJAVADOC-181] Javadoc report not generated for multi-module project if run from parent level.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-181</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For the following project design (s. attached testcase):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;parent&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;#45; library        // javadoc:aggregate!&lt;br/&gt;
     &amp;#45; module-a&lt;br/&gt;
     &amp;#45; module-b&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;#45; application&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;javadoc report for &apos;library&apos; is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; generated (not invoked), if &apos;mvn site&apos; is&lt;br/&gt;
called at &apos;parent&apos; level (but is properly done if run at &apos;library&apos; level itself).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>W2K, JDK 6u5, Maven 2.0.8</environment>
        <key id="12804310">MJAVADOC-181</key>
            <summary>Javadoc report not generated for multi-module project if run from parent level.</summary>
